  "text": "To illustrate the point of the paper, we will consider a problem for which an ILMI approach was recently proposed [CITATION_1] . This problem is the design of a reduced-order positive filter for linear systems. Positive systems, found in many areas (see [CITATION_2] ), are dynamic systems with state variables and outputs positive at all times. The filter to be designed has to estimate an unmeasured output (z) of a system (Σ) from the measurements (y), with minimum objective value chosen as the H ∞ norm of the filtering error transfer function (G) between the exogenous disturbance signal (w) and the error (e): the difference between the output (z) and its estimate (ẑ). Details on the problem motivations and challenges are given in the introduction of [CITATION_3] , here only the elements necessary to reproduce the contribution are recalled.",
